reviewText: Unimpressed, even a little disgusted.  I rented the movie based on the half dozen reviews available at the time; man, do I feel duped.  There's nothing funny about it (unless you're in the 4th grade and find profanity and vulgarity for its own sake hilarious, or you find gay humor funny).  And it is certainly a let down as a vampire film as well.  Not sure what was trying to be accomplished, but I couldn't even make it through 20 minutes.Bad acting, poor writing, and worse directing.  Save your money, and your time.
summary: Horrible Movie...Don't Recommend Unless Flaming Homosexuality and Blatant Vulgarity is Your Thing

reviewText: The story is that a young man learns that he's a reincarnated vampire king. The story is flimsy at best and you can pretty much discard it. In fact, just about every effort to insert the premise behind why he's targeted to be turned into a vampire is kind of distracting and almost pointless. Ladies and gentlemen. Here's the real story: Young flamboyant man becomes a vampire. The rest of the movie is kind of just killing people.I'm a fan of vampire movies so I thought I'd try it out. It's not what I expected, but I found it entertaining, though I feel like it missed it's mark. As I mentioned earlier the story is heavily flawed and and because of this, the movie is just held together by the main character. Martin Yurkovic plays Carmen, a failed actor who is "turned" by 2 vampires who knew him in a previous incarnation. His role is that of a flamboyant and mildly aggressive homosexual man who is besties with a girl and a straight guy. I feel like Martin turned a crappy character into something half entertaining, though I don't think I ever actually laughed. Most of my enjoyment was just watching his antics. Dark humor, at times almost slapstick.Oh the actual movie was horrible. I think if the story was actually good, you'd notice the other actors, who were mostly terrible. 3 stars for originality, though. Plus there was no sparkly vampires or tortured souls. That was refreshing.
summary: It's kind of gay. Not that there's anything wrong with that.

reviewText: There is absolutely nothing in this movie that needs to be in 3-D. This is another case of jacking up the price on a movie by slapping 3-D on the cover. I don't think this is the worst movie I've ever seen, but the acting was really bad. Maybe if the writers had given the actors something better to work with.... There isn't enough camp to make this campy, not enough horror to make this a horror film, and nothing funny to make this a comedy. I'm sorry that I have to give it such a crappy review because my daughter is in it, and I wish it had been better.

reviewText: The best part of this movie:  newly turned vampire "hero" drinks from a salon-worker and complains that her blood tastes like nail polish remover. His vampire companion chides him for wasting blood - "Don't you know there are vampires in Africa that are starving to death?"No part of the "plot" of this movie makes any sense.  Not one.
